Cost	API Fees + Infrastructure	Token Cost + Local I/O

Architect's Brief: Recommendations for Production

1. Enforce Idempotency: Ensure all tool calls (emails, file writes) use unique keys to prevent double-execution during retry loops.
2. Verify via Citations: For agents operating on codebases or dynamic files, implement JIT verification to ensure the agent never acts on stale "memories" of a file that has been modified.
3. Target the "Mute Agent": Engineering efforts should prioritize Conflict Resolution. An agent that asks for your name twice is a chatbot; an agent that silently updates your infrastructure based on a preference expressed three weeks ago is a digital twin.

The future of agency is a systems engineering problem, not a model selection problem. The intelligence of an agent is fundamentally capped by the architecture of its memory.
